Source: The Miami Herald Online, Sat 14 Jul 2001 [edited
<http://www.miami.com/herald>

West Nile Virus Found in More Crows in North Florida
----------------------------------------------------
TALLAHASSEE: Health officials say they have discovered signs of the
potentially deadly West Nile virus in 3 more crow carcasses found in
North Florida. After a crow tested positive for the encephalitis-causing
virus last week, the first known case ever in Florida, the state Health
Department asked Floridians to notify health officials of any dead birds
they found.
--
